WEBVTT

00:12.291 --> 00:13.333
(screams)
(tires screeching)

00:13.417 --> 00:16.000
RAY: What happened?
EZRA: I fucking hit someone.

00:16.083 --> 00:18.375
I dragged his body to the car
and put him in the trunk.

00:18.458 --> 00:20.542
STEVE:
You took me off
a real homicide

00:20.625 --> 00:22.166
for a fucking log?

00:22.250 --> 00:23.917
RAY:
What the fuck
are you doing?

00:24.000 --> 00:26.000
Fuck me, Ray.

00:26.083 --> 00:28.333
LENA:
Abby's here. At the office.
RAY: Get over

00:28.417 --> 00:30.417
to my apartment right away.
I got a girl handcuffed

00:30.500 --> 00:32.583
to my towel rack.
Hey...

00:32.667 --> 00:34.125
Is there anyone I
need to worry about?

00:34.208 --> 00:35.333
FRANCES:
No.

00:35.417 --> 00:36.667
BOY:
Mom, come on.
Let's go.

00:39.500 --> 00:41.583
ARAM:
This place is great.
A good investment.

00:41.667 --> 00:44.333
You think?
Sure.

00:44.417 --> 00:46.583
AVI:
Mickey's met with him
a couple of times.

00:46.667 --> 00:48.125
RAY:
Avi, something's up.

00:48.208 --> 00:49.417
What are we gonna do?

00:49.500 --> 00:50.041
Your father's been here.

00:50.125 --> 00:51.792
What did you say to him?

00:51.875 --> 00:52.875
I don't remember.

00:52.959 --> 00:54.291
You don't have a fucking choice.

00:54.375 --> 00:54.667
You have to remember.

00:54.750 --> 00:56.959
I can't.

00:57.041 --> 00:58.917
I have a brain tumor.

01:06.709 --> 01:09.000
Who the fuck
are you, Ray?

01:21.000 --> 01:23.333
♪ ♪

01:43.458 --> 01:45.000
Ray?

01:45.083 --> 01:47.500
Motherfucker.
Hey! What...

01:50.000 --> 01:51.583
What the fuck, Ray?!

01:51.667 --> 01:52.625
How's the water, Frank?

01:52.709 --> 01:54.166
It's fucking cold!

01:54.250 --> 01:56.250
The fuck am I paying you for?

01:56.333 --> 01:58.250
You open an investigation on me
without saying anything?

01:58.333 --> 02:00.166
I don't know what the fuck
you're talking about, Ray.

02:00.250 --> 02:01.875
I told you last time, didn't I?

02:01.959 --> 02:03.834
We haven't had shit
on you in years.

02:03.917 --> 02:06.041
Who the fuck is this?

02:07.333 --> 02:08.959
That's Van Miller.

02:09.041 --> 02:10.041
He one of yours?

02:10.125 --> 02:12.625
Yeah, he's one of ours.

02:12.709 --> 02:14.792
(shouts)
Goddamn it, Ray!

02:14.875 --> 02:16.375
Why's he talking to my father?

02:16.458 --> 02:17.959
I thought your father
was still in prison.

02:18.041 --> 02:20.083
He got out!
You know anything about that?

02:20.166 --> 02:21.834
No. (shouts)

02:21.917 --> 02:23.208
Goddamn it, Ray!
No? Well, you better

02:23.291 --> 02:26.291
fucking find out
or I'll tell your wife

02:26.375 --> 02:28.542
about that kid you support
in Riverside.
Jesus, Ray,

02:28.625 --> 02:30.458
I'm with the fucking FBI.

02:32.625 --> 02:35.458
Fuck.

02:35.542 --> 02:37.000
Give me your
fucking hand.

02:37.083 --> 02:38.667
Give me your fucking hand.

02:43.625 --> 02:46.041
(groans)
Damn it, Ray.

02:46.125 --> 02:47.750
What do you know
about Miller?

02:47.834 --> 02:49.875
He works alone.

02:49.959 --> 02:52.667
He gets shit done.

02:52.750 --> 02:54.417
He's good.

02:54.500 --> 02:56.750
If you think he's after you,
he probably is.

02:56.834 --> 02:59.250
Shut it down.

02:59.333 --> 03:02.917
It doesn't work that way.

03:06.709 --> 03:08.792
Ray...

03:10.166 --> 03:12.041
Ray.

03:12.125 --> 03:13.917
(cell phone chimes)

03:14.000 --> 03:16.417
(Bridget chuckles)

03:19.125 --> 03:22.333
Enough.
I'm almost done.

03:22.417 --> 03:25.417
If that's that boy, Bridg,
all I'm gonna say is...
Don't.

03:25.500 --> 03:27.750
The look on your
face says it all.

03:27.834 --> 03:29.750
Uncle Bunchy's having
a party. Can we go?

03:29.834 --> 03:30.792
You're grounded.

03:30.875 --> 03:32.125
Since when does he get his phone
if he's grounded?

03:32.208 --> 03:34.875
ABBY:
It's for emergencies.
Can I go?

03:34.959 --> 03:36.500
It's a housewarming.

03:38.834 --> 03:40.709
Bunchy bought a house?

03:41.875 --> 03:43.959
For who?

03:44.041 --> 03:45.458
For him and Mick.

03:45.542 --> 03:47.500
He didn't tell me
he was buying a house.

03:47.583 --> 03:48.709
What, he didn't ask
your permission?
BRIDGET: Can I?

03:48.792 --> 03:51.250
No.

03:51.333 --> 03:53.417
Nobody goes to that house.
And if Mickey calls

03:53.500 --> 03:56.125
either of you again,
I want to know about it.

03:56.208 --> 03:59.291
Jesus.

04:01.792 --> 04:03.583
(coffee pouring)
All right.

04:03.667 --> 04:05.750
Let's go.

04:06.417 --> 04:09.000
Did you put on deodorant?

04:09.083 --> 04:11.208
(sighs)

04:12.792 --> 04:14.417
Where you been?

04:18.000 --> 04:19.542
Nowhere.

04:19.625 --> 04:21.709
Really?

04:21.792 --> 04:23.709
Why are your pants wet?

04:25.792 --> 04:27.166
The marina.

04:27.250 --> 04:28.750
The marina?
Yeah.

04:28.834 --> 04:29.709
Are you buying a boat?

04:29.792 --> 04:31.000
You mad at me?

04:31.083 --> 04:33.792
I'm not mad at you.

04:33.875 --> 04:35.542
I just don't get you anymore.

04:35.625 --> 04:37.917
The handcuffs.
The dead priest.

04:39.792 --> 04:42.166
Is that the guy
that abused Bunchy?

04:42.250 --> 04:44.125
Come on, Abs, you know
I can't talk about business.

04:44.208 --> 04:46.917
How is that business, Ray?

04:48.333 --> 04:51.166
See, this is
what I'm talking about.

04:57.750 --> 04:59.417
This is it, just behind
the frontal sinus.

04:59.500 --> 05:01.792
But the incision
is going to be right...

05:01.875 --> 05:04.625
there.

05:04.709 --> 05:07.792
Just a little nick in
the shape of an eyelash,

05:07.875 --> 05:10.542
just enough for the laser
to get in and zap the tumor.

05:10.625 --> 05:12.375
And that's it?

05:12.458 --> 05:15.458
Well, we won't know until we
start hitting it with radiation.

05:15.542 --> 05:17.834
What we need to avoid
is the optic nerve.

05:17.917 --> 05:19.458
That is a biggie.

05:19.542 --> 05:22.542
All right, so I'll see
you in a couple hours.

05:24.291 --> 05:25.375
What's he gonna do?
It's going to be okay.

05:25.458 --> 05:28.375
He's, uh, going
to shrink the tumor.

05:28.458 --> 05:30.166
No! What are they doing?

05:30.250 --> 05:33.208
Are they shaving my head?
I pride myself on my hair.

05:33.291 --> 05:34.417
You know that.
I know that. I know that.

05:34.500 --> 05:37.500
Just a little bit,
sweetheart.
Where's Ray?

05:37.583 --> 05:40.792
I want to talk to Ray.
Uh... Okay.

05:40.875 --> 05:42.709
(Mickey grunting)

05:42.792 --> 05:45.625
MICKEY:
Shit, don't
scrape nothing.

05:45.709 --> 05:46.917
(chuckles)

05:47.000 --> 05:50.041
(grunts)

05:50.125 --> 05:51.917
Ah, it's coming together. See?

05:52.000 --> 05:54.417
Ha.
Yeah.

05:54.500 --> 05:57.792
Your little SNAP group
really come through.

05:57.875 --> 05:59.375
Three couches.

05:59.458 --> 06:02.417
(grunts)
Got to give
those Snappers credit.

06:02.500 --> 06:04.542
I don't know.
Hey.

06:04.625 --> 06:05.959
You just bought a house.
Where's your...

06:06.041 --> 06:07.750
where's your gusto? Huh?

06:07.834 --> 06:10.000
And why not get
some new furniture?

06:10.083 --> 06:11.500
New furniture.
Little accessories.

06:11.583 --> 06:15.250
Ray's gonna be so fucking pissed
I bought this place.

06:15.333 --> 06:18.125
I'm not supposed to be spending
so much money.

06:18.208 --> 06:19.083
Ah, bullshit.

06:19.166 --> 06:20.959
Maybe you are a bad influence.

06:21.041 --> 06:25.291
Whoa. Wow.

06:25.375 --> 06:28.875
All right, then.

06:31.500 --> 06:34.625
But the decor really
could use a woman's touch.

06:34.709 --> 06:37.625
What, hookers?

06:37.709 --> 06:39.625
Knock it off.

06:39.709 --> 06:42.709
Who you calling?

06:42.792 --> 06:45.125
(phone ringing)

06:47.208 --> 06:48.041
Hello?

06:48.125 --> 06:48.750
It's your father-in-law.

06:48.834 --> 06:51.500
Hi, Mick.

06:51.583 --> 06:54.917
Abby, look. I want to respect
Ray's boundary issues.

06:55.000 --> 06:56.125
I do.

06:56.208 --> 06:58.166
Uh-huh.

06:58.250 --> 06:59.667
Look, uh...

06:59.750 --> 07:02.125
I got a little bit
of a situation right now.

07:02.208 --> 07:03.709
Uh, I'm out of my depth here.

07:03.792 --> 07:05.250
Bunchy is freaking out.

07:05.333 --> 07:06.917
He's very fragile.

07:07.000 --> 07:08.041
What's wrong?

07:08.125 --> 07:09.667
Well, it's the house.

07:09.750 --> 07:11.667
Probably could've done better
for the money,

07:11.750 --> 07:17.250
and, uh... all he's got here
is a bunch of, frankly,

07:17.333 --> 07:18.000
pretty disgusting furniture.

07:18.083 --> 07:21.166
All right, listen.

07:21.250 --> 07:23.667
Let me see if I can stop by
after lunch, okay?

07:23.750 --> 07:27.333
Abby, thank you.
From the bottom of my heart.

07:27.417 --> 07:28.709
All right.

07:28.792 --> 07:31.625
Bye.

07:37.917 --> 07:40.875
Voilà.

07:40.959 --> 07:43.375
(indistinct chatter)

07:53.250 --> 07:55.166
Is that a new suit?

07:58.333 --> 08:01.542
I just haven't seen
you wear it before, is all.

08:01.625 --> 08:03.834
It's nice.
I would like the turkey
chili, a bread bowl

08:03.917 --> 08:05.583
and a Polish sausage, sliced
lengthwise down the middle.

08:08.667 --> 08:09.750
And you, sir?

08:09.834 --> 08:12.792
May I have a cup
of coffee, please?

08:27.250 --> 08:29.625
(Van shaking
packet)

08:54.625 --> 08:58.583
Uh, could you hand me
some napkins, please?

09:04.542 --> 09:07.291
Thank you very much.

09:20.917 --> 09:22.625
(sighs)

09:22.709 --> 09:25.291
(sighs)

09:25.375 --> 09:29.583
(woman chuckles, exhales)
(man moans)

09:29.667 --> 09:33.291
(moaning)
(exhales)

09:33.375 --> 09:36.625
Got to be a backdoor man, baby.

09:36.709 --> 09:38.792
At least while we're getting
to know each other.

09:38.875 --> 09:43.083
NBA star's got
to be careful, huh?
Yeah.

09:47.125 --> 09:50.500
(phone rings)

09:52.000 --> 09:53.917
Yeah.

09:54.000 --> 09:56.667
(quietly):
Deonte Brown just checked in
with a club girl.

09:56.750 --> 09:57.750
Goddamn it.

09:57.834 --> 09:59.000
That's not all.

09:59.083 --> 09:59.667
It's the limo driver.

09:59.750 --> 10:01.709
Every time he pulls up,

10:01.792 --> 10:02.750
some girl hits the NBA lottery
nine months later.

10:33.750 --> 10:35.500
(plopping into liquid)

10:50.875 --> 10:52.750
(plopping)

10:58.166 --> 11:00.208
(dialing)

11:00.291 --> 11:01.667
(line ringing)

11:01.750 --> 11:04.125
(cell phone ringtone playing)

11:12.125 --> 11:14.500
Hello?

11:14.583 --> 11:15.917
Deonte, stop.

11:16.000 --> 11:16.583
Stop what?

11:16.667 --> 11:18.917
Stop fucking that girl.

11:19.000 --> 11:20.542
I'm not fucking her, dawg.

11:20.625 --> 11:22.166
No. Deonte?

11:22.250 --> 11:23.333
Oh, shit!

11:23.417 --> 11:26.125
DEONTE:
What you doing, girl?
Deonte, I mean it!

11:26.208 --> 11:28.166
Wait. Wait! Hold on. Oh.

11:28.250 --> 11:29.125
No, n-no.

11:29.208 --> 11:30.792
Hey, Deonte!

11:30.875 --> 11:32.709
Oh! Shit! Oh!

11:32.792 --> 11:36.166
Hey! You stupid fuck!

11:36.250 --> 11:37.625
(sighs)

11:39.125 --> 11:41.709
(sighs)

11:43.625 --> 11:47.083
That was the truth.

11:47.166 --> 11:48.792
What's your name again?

11:55.041 --> 11:56.417
Baby, I'm just gonna get this
out of here.

11:56.500 --> 11:58.667
It is your will.

12:14.041 --> 12:15.208
(water running)

12:15.291 --> 12:16.709
Okay.

12:16.792 --> 12:20.375
(toilet flushing,
water continues running)

12:27.792 --> 12:28.959
(chitters)

12:48.291 --> 12:49.583
(door opens and closes)

12:49.667 --> 12:52.375
(phone ringing)

12:52.458 --> 12:54.000
(phone chimes)

12:54.083 --> 12:55.417
DEB:
Ezra's asking for you.

12:55.500 --> 12:57.375
He's very agitated.

12:57.458 --> 12:59.917
I'll be there as soon as I can,
Deb, I promise.

13:04.834 --> 13:06.625
(sighs)

13:11.917 --> 13:14.709
♪ ♪

13:26.333 --> 13:29.291
(monkey squeaking)

13:29.375 --> 13:31.291
(chittering)

13:31.375 --> 13:32.709
(sighs)

13:32.792 --> 13:35.667
(chitters)

13:37.125 --> 13:39.333
(chittering)

13:41.125 --> 13:43.250
(chittering)

13:46.625 --> 13:49.041
Van?

13:49.125 --> 13:50.500
Huh?

13:52.959 --> 13:55.875
You all right, buddy?

13:56.417 --> 13:58.959
Uh, I...

13:59.041 --> 14:02.959
Hey. No, no. Wait. No,
no, no. Sorry. Just...

14:29.333 --> 14:31.417
(grunting)

14:31.500 --> 14:33.083
Open the trunk.

14:33.166 --> 14:35.333
(soft grunting)
Open it.

14:35.417 --> 14:37.125
(grunts softly)

14:40.792 --> 14:41.625
Deonte Brown?

14:41.709 --> 14:45.250
Off limits, understand?

14:45.333 --> 14:46.959
(grunting)

14:47.041 --> 14:47.625
Understand?

14:47.709 --> 14:50.375
(muffled utterance)

14:50.458 --> 14:53.792
(siren whoops)

14:55.125 --> 14:57.291
Oh.

15:02.875 --> 15:04.959
(garbled radio transmission)

15:10.041 --> 15:11.417
(gasps)

15:11.500 --> 15:13.125
(panting)

15:17.542 --> 15:20.458
Do you have any idea how
fast you were going, sir?

15:22.625 --> 15:25.041
100?
No.

15:25.125 --> 15:26.000
200?

15:26.083 --> 15:29.375
Sir, you were going
three miles an hour.

15:29.458 --> 15:30.834
Three miles. Wow.

15:30.917 --> 15:33.083
License, registration,
proof of insurance.

15:40.917 --> 15:44.250
(panting)

15:44.333 --> 15:45.583
What are you
doing, sir?

15:45.667 --> 15:47.500
Give me that.
I... Oh.

15:47.583 --> 15:50.000
(panting)

15:50.083 --> 15:51.750
Special Agent Miller?

15:51.834 --> 15:54.000
(laughing):
No. No, I... No.

15:54.083 --> 15:56.542
Step out of the
car, please.

16:00.250 --> 16:01.208
(sighs)

16:01.291 --> 16:03.792
You seem a little
under the weather.
I am.

16:03.875 --> 16:07.375
I am having a terrible day.

16:11.917 --> 16:13.458
(grunts softly)

16:13.542 --> 16:15.250
(panting)

16:15.333 --> 16:17.375
Look, I'm going to have to
cite you for reckless driving.

16:17.458 --> 16:18.709
Oh, God.

16:18.792 --> 16:21.333
Sir, have you been drinking?

16:21.417 --> 16:23.375
I had...

16:23.458 --> 16:26.917
a small amount of orange juice
at my home,

16:27.000 --> 16:31.792
and one cup of coffee
with two Equals and some cream.

16:31.875 --> 16:33.083
I'm going to have
to perform a few tests, sir.

16:36.458 --> 16:38.667
You have an incredible voice.

16:38.750 --> 16:40.875
A truly
remarkable voice.

16:40.959 --> 16:43.291
That's fine. Now, I'd like you
to raise your right arm...

16:43.375 --> 16:45.375
Okay.
...and then touch
your finger to your nose.

16:48.291 --> 16:50.625
(knocking)

16:51.792 --> 16:55.041
Abby, thank you for coming.

16:55.125 --> 16:56.792
We're lost at sea.

16:56.875 --> 16:57.834
I wish we could see
more of you.

16:57.917 --> 17:00.417
Here.
You know how things are.

17:05.667 --> 17:07.291
It's charming.

17:10.333 --> 17:12.542
That's a nice piece.

17:12.625 --> 17:14.917
Yeah.

17:27.917 --> 17:29.458
(groans)
Home, sweet home.

17:38.583 --> 17:40.792
(dialing)

17:40.875 --> 17:42.792
(line ringing)

17:42.875 --> 17:44.792
RAY:
Hello?
Yeah. He's home.

17:44.875 --> 17:46.667
Good. Thanks.

17:51.625 --> 17:52.917
Dawg!

17:53.000 --> 17:55.959
What's up, bro?
What you doing here?

17:56.041 --> 17:58.000
You, get the fuck
out of here now.

18:04.125 --> 18:05.834
Ass and mouth, dawg.
I protected myself.

18:05.917 --> 18:08.000
Yeah? Where'd this come from?

18:08.083 --> 18:11.333
(cell phone ringtone plays)
Huh?

18:11.417 --> 18:13.709
Can I get my...?
Oh.

18:13.792 --> 18:15.750
Look at that.

18:17.583 --> 18:19.917
How many kids do you have,
Deonte?

18:20.000 --> 18:21.125
Deonte Junior,
Deonte the Second...

18:21.208 --> 18:24.917
This was Deonte the Third.
What you doing, Ray?

18:25.000 --> 18:27.333
Calling your wife back so she
can jog your fucking memory.

18:27.417 --> 18:28.834
Whoa. No, no,
don't do that.

18:28.917 --> 18:31.041
(line ringing)
That would be a bad idea.

18:31.125 --> 18:32.792
MRS. BROWN:
Where the fuck have you been?

18:32.875 --> 18:34.333
She sounds pissed.

18:34.417 --> 18:36.417
Hello? Hello?
I'm sorry, okay?
I'm sorry.

18:36.500 --> 18:37.333
Deonte?

18:37.417 --> 18:40.333
Deonte?
How much did you make last year?

18:40.417 --> 18:42.333
I'm talking to you, Deonte.
Uh, $30 million?

18:42.417 --> 18:44.166
What the fuck is wrong with you?

18:44.250 --> 18:46.083
Deonte, this is some bullshit.
Where are you at?

18:46.166 --> 18:48.417
I know. I know.
Never again, Ray.

18:48.500 --> 18:50.333
You keep this shit up,
you're gonna lose your sponsors.

18:50.417 --> 18:51.750
You'll end up teaching
the pick-and-roll

18:51.834 --> 18:53.166
to a bunch
of fucking fifth graders.

18:53.250 --> 18:53.875
All right?
All right.

18:53.959 --> 18:55.208
You better say something.

18:55.291 --> 18:57.917
I'm not playing
with you this time.

18:58.000 --> 19:00.208
Hello?

19:00.291 --> 19:01.625
Hel-lo!

19:01.709 --> 19:03.667
Deonte!
(door opens and closes)

19:03.750 --> 19:05.375
Babe, hey.

19:05.458 --> 19:08.500
WOMAN (over P.A.):
Any available nurse to room...

19:08.583 --> 19:10.750
Ray will be here any minute,
sweetheart.

19:24.500 --> 19:26.458
(gasping)

19:26.542 --> 19:29.041
(panting)

19:30.333 --> 19:32.000
Oh.

19:33.250 --> 19:35.583
(panting)

19:50.625 --> 19:53.417
(panting)

19:55.834 --> 19:57.458
(panting)

20:06.333 --> 20:07.875
Oh, my friend.

20:07.959 --> 20:10.417
My friend.

20:10.500 --> 20:12.750
Okay. Okay.

20:13.709 --> 20:15.834
(man grunting)

20:17.625 --> 20:19.166
(gasps)
Wh...

20:19.250 --> 20:20.166
(grunts)

20:20.250 --> 20:20.750
(shouts)

20:20.834 --> 20:23.375
(groans)

20:23.458 --> 20:25.375
(motorcycle revving)

20:25.458 --> 20:28.041
(laughing, whooping)

20:28.125 --> 20:30.834
(motorcycle approaching)

20:37.792 --> 20:40.000
(laughs, shouts)

20:40.083 --> 20:42.750
(automatic gunfire,
bullets ricocheting)

20:50.208 --> 20:53.000
